189. namque] The mention of Cupavo's erest leads Verg. to tell the story of how Cycnus, in excessive grief for Phaethon, pined away, and became a swan. The sisters of Phaethon had been turned into poplar trees after his death (umbram sororum). Cp. Ov. M. ii. 333 ff.
